text: Hi. Has the name of the peer docker image been changed lately? I did `docker images | grep peer` and now I see `hyperledger/fabric-peer`, wasn't it `hyperledger-peer` before?

at least, all the images that the build system directly generates
some of the chaincode containers still have wonky names like dev-jdoe-xxx

With latest code , after make clean I see the below error
make: *** No rule to make target `sdk/node/doc/assets/js/modernizr.js', needed by `build/image/src/.dummy'.  Stop.
